Database Type and Version (Oracle)
Platform: PortSwigger Web Security Academy

Difficulty: Practitioner

Status: Solved

Objective
Display the database version string by injecting into the product category filter.

Vulnerability
The application is vulnerable to UNION-based SQL injection. However, Oracle databases have two strict requirements that make this a "Practitioner" level challenge:

Every SELECT statement must include a table name (using the DUAL table for testing).

The UNION columns must match the data types of the original query.

Payload Used
First, determine the number of columns (found to be 2) and their types (both string). Then, use the Oracle-specific version table:

'+UNION+SELECT+BANNER,+NULL+FROM+v$version--

Why It Works
v$version: This is a built-in dynamic performance view in Oracle that contains the database version details.

BANNER: This is the specific column name within v$version that holds the version string.

--: The comment character in Oracle used to nullify the rest of the original SQL query.

Impact
Information Disclosure (Database finger-printing).

Allows an attacker to tailor further exploits based on known vulnerabilities for that specific Oracle version.
